Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{1}(chopped into 2cm chunks, no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{a drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over half the @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a medium #saucepan{} with a #tight-fitting lid{}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{0.25%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the #lid{}.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, halve the @green pepper{1}(halved and chopped into 2cm chunks) and discard the core and seeds.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and pepper chunks and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and golden, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Once the pepper has softened, stir in the garlic and remaining Cajun spice mix and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{0.5%carton}, @BBQ sauce{32%g}, kidney beans, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water for the sauce{150%ml} to the pan, then season with salt and pepper.

Stir together, then bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once thickened, stir the roasted sweet potato through the chilli.

Add a splash of water to loosen if you feel it needs it. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{} and spoon the sweet potato chilli over the top.

Finish with a dollop of @soured cream{75%g} and a sprinkle of cheese.

Enjoy!